issue.title: FreeBSD compatibility patch

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
* Treat the 'amd64' architecture the same way as 'x86_64'
* Use thr_self() instead of gettid() on FreeBSD

body: You should be able to easily reproduce this with the latest clang compiler. This is basically a clang compatibility issue.
I can confirm the same errors are thrown on my Mac with OS X 10.15.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?

To resolve #2271
